<br>
Even in the post you refer to Holt, the cleric states that he uses CoHeal against single uber mobs.  I have no problem with how clerics heal normally, as long as I'm standing, I'm happy.<br>
<br>
The problem I have is when I get a bunch of whiny clerics telling me that they can't cast CoHeal because they'll get aggro.  This is a crock of crap.  Granted this did occur when they did the healing aggro patch initially, but since they've toned it down, I've seen plenty of clerics casting CoHeal without drawing aggro.<br>
<br>
Celestial Healing does 750hps of healing over 4 ticks.  The first tick it does no healing.  It also has a 4 second casting time.<br>
<br>
Divine Light does 900hps of healing.  Cast time is 4 seconds as well.<br>
<br>
Complete Healing does unlimited Healing in 10 seconds.<br>
<br>
Now, let's assume that most clerics use Celestial Healing, followed by a Divine Light (as I'm told most do since the healling aggro patch).  Tank will get 1650 hps, over 12 seconds.  In the same 12 seconds against Maestro, I took 6k hps of damage.  Celestial healing and Divine Light simply do not provide enough HP recovery to offset the damage that he's dishing out.<br>
<br>
We have more problems than this fighting Maestro though as well.  Our tanks should not be &quot;taunting&quot; every time their taunt button refreshes.  One tank needs to get aggro, and keep it.  Having the mob bouncing around does not work.  If most of the damage is distributed to one or two tanks, it would make the healing much easier for the clerics. <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 56 Knight<br>
Amnesty<br>
Member of Saryrn Guild Alliance</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard>saryrnguildallianceboard</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://www.qksrv.net/click-553273-1925262" target="_blank" >
